Dear Claudio,

> If F is left adjoint to G : D --> C and there is a natural isomorphism
> FG --> 1_D (not necessarily the counit), then G is full and faithful.

A proof of the (dual) claim you find as the proof of Lemma 8.1 of my course
on basic category theory

      www.mathematik.tu-darmstadt.de/~streicher/CTCL.pdf.gz

on p.45.

